          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bla_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Findlay, OH 3/9/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.82)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=1361'>brad "swccguy" eier</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=1361&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 10, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Well so after doing bad at bash-con a few weeks ago I decide my deck needs some changes.  I take out paths and strength of spirits and stuff, and add more condition removal, ans some rare boromir and armor.  I test it a little and it seems to run a lot better.  I go into the tourney feeling pretty confident.<br>
<br>
When the store got the moria starters in they also got a booster box.  one of the employees, a lotr player, proceeded to open it.  later I found out from our rider that it was supposed to be prize support for the tourney, oh well.  <br>
<br>
So anyway Saturday rolls around and its crazy outside.  I guess a tornado hit down or something.  Man I drove to the card store dodging fallen trees and power lines and trying not to get blown away by the wind. <br>
<br>
I get there and they tell me some people from michigan called and are coming.  I don&#39;t know if they will make it because of the weather though.  But sure enough they come rollin in and we trade and talk a little then we play.<br>
<br>
the deck-<br>
Gandalf start. bid 5 get sam.  use aimed archery and events to add/subtract strength in skirmishes.  shadow nazgul.  2 of the 7 best ones, 3 skulker and balrog.  some blade tip/breath action.  a few relentless charge, all blades perish and some card for against allies.<br>
<br>
game 1 vs Dan Joyce 1544 Don&#39;t pee in the pool<br>
Well his deck seemed to be a carbon copy of don&#39;t pee in the pool, you know the aragorn/frodo deck that tries to overwhelm with insane moria swarms.  So I bid and go first.  I drop Boromir and move.  he gets out a scavenger so I suck up a wound.  I go on to 3 even with a big pool.  He is able to drop a few more guys.  luckily he doesn&#39;t have denizens enraged so frodo lives and i just take a few wounds.  His fellowship turns he always moved 1 site.  I would play at most 1 nazgul and he would kill it.  thats how it was every turn.  My next fellowship i&#39;m still trying to find an archer.  I decide that if my opponent is only moving 1 a turn then i will too.  No point in risking a beatdown.  Every site he gets out hordes of guys but i&#39;m able to soak up wounds.  I play albert dreary and sleep away his stacked goblin swarms which is huge.  about site 6 y archers show up and its time to rock and roll (after i get past site 7 no archery).  at site 8 he plays 8 minions including a troll.  i shoot about 4, Boromir sucks the troll twice (armor) and I survive.  He moves his 1 a turn i drop a witch king who gets jacked.   it didn&#39;t matter though.  I move to 9 with 4 companions out and he can only play about 2 minions so i win.<br>
fw3<br>
hi-win<br>
lo-nothing<br>
<br>
game 2 vs Kyle? Baird 1621 ranger/nazgul<br>
I bid hi, go first get sam.  play boromir and move.  he plays a fierce nazgul.  I take 2 wounds and decide with 8 pool left and 1 already out that i can&#39;t move to the ford yet.  His turn he drops aragorn, athelas and ranger sword, moves.  i play nelya who gets shot then killed.  he goes to 3 and i have nothing.  i move to 3, take more wounds and have to stop.  the game goes on like this.  he moves and i&#39;m catching up but he&#39;s ahead.  I kill arewen and balrog kills gandalf.  he is 1 site ahoead though and goes to 9 and i dot have any minion to play.<br>
fl1<br>
4<br>
hi-?<br>
lo- he told me if i would have moved to 3 he had no minions in his hand. gosh darnit.<br>
<br>
3 vs demetrius Lemanski 1738 big fellowship/nazgul<br>
His deck was interesting.  the only thing i ca compare it to on decktech is mabey the dominator.  he had 8 companions, 8 stealth, 4 paths, bunch of bounder and sleep.<br>
he wins the bid and goes first. He strolls right along to 3, sucking up a few wounds.  mmeanwhile my fellowship is struggling.  i scrapo and fight my way to 3, barely holding on.  By this time he is moving to site 7. yes his expendable fellowship just sucks up wounds the die then he plays more the next turn.  the balrog and some random nazzgul kill off a few companions.  i know i have no chance of winning but i play it out to see what happens.  i move to 5 ad get jumped by balrog and stuff but i&#39;m ok.  he moves to 8 and when the fog cleared he has just agarorn and frodo with blade tips/breaths on them.  I move to 6 or 7 and just dump cards from my hand.  He moves to 9, here we go.  I draw 3 cards cause he has 3 burdens.  aragorn is exhausted.  he has 2 bounder out.  i morgul gates witchking, gates cantea.  aragorn dies to king.  frodo plays paths x 3 on cantea.  i&#39;m about ready to lose him when i look at my had and say....&quot;all blades perish! &quot; boo-yeah.  so frodo is exhausted and has to take 2 burdens.  fierce i have 26 on frodo but he has bounder and lots of pump cards, but he has to take 2 burdens since he has the ring on. 3+ 3+ 2+ 2=10, frodo is corrupted without a single corrpution card in the deck. wow, what a finish.<br>
fw3<br>
7<br>
hi-wow my minions won it for me, it never happens<br>
lo- without that all blades he would have won<br>
<br>
4 vs Adam PUBES Huber 1706 random guys/nazgul<br>
well pubes is undefeated so i need to beat him to claim my first toyrney victory.  we both start gandalf. i go first.  my fellowship totally flipped out and kicked him in the face when i drop aragorn and like 4 cards on him, and boromir.  he doesn&#39;t draw a minion till site 5 that blows.  meanwhile his fellowship is not working well and i kill a couple of hobbits fast.  i double move all the way to 5, then i decide to slow down. he&#39;s 3 sites behind me so i just start going 1 a turn.  i actually get worried being so far ahead after what happened last game.  i move to 8 he plays nothing.  Galdalf gets tip/breath and exhausted.  He moves to 5 i balrog which is cool.  he goes to 6 then stops.<br>
my turn gandalf dies. i go to 9. he plays 2 nazgul.  i make aragorn defender +1, he takes both of them the first time. 2nd time boromir and legolas die to them.....but that means that frodo lives! so i win<br>
fw 3<br>
10<br>
<br>
so theres a 3way (ooohhh....3way) tie for first, like at every tourney i&#39;m in.  but this time i win! allright<br>
final standings<br>
1 me<br>
2 pubes<br>
3 paul<br>
4 demetrius<br>
5 kyle<br>
6 dan<br>
7 shae<br>
8 egon<br>
<br>
so anyway we have a few random rares instead of moria for prizes which blows.  <br>
<br>
props and slops<br>
props<br>
-me for winning<br>
-everyone who came<br>
-demetrius/kyle for driving 3 hours thru a tornado to play<br>
-ninjas for being sweet, and by sweet i mean totally awesome<br>
-gandalf for being a ninja and flipping out and killing people.<br>
<br>
slops<br>
-weather for sucking<br>
-people who take your prize support<br>
 <br>
<br>
later<br>
brad eier <br>
bacon2 <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3482&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
